## 📈 Pipeline

\`\`\`
Raw Data → EDA → Preprocessing → Feature Scaling → Model Training → Evaluation → Deployment
\`\`\`

### Step 1: EDA (Exploratory Data Analysis)
- Load 768 patient records
- Check for missing/invalid values
- Analyze feature correlations
- Detect class imbalance (ratio 0.54:1)
- Visualize distributions

### Step 2: Preprocessing
- Drop weakly correlated features (SkinThickness, Insulin)
- Remove rows with invalid zeros
- Split: 80% train, 20% test (stratified)
- Scale features using StandardScaler

### Step 3: Model Training
- Train Logistic Regression (baseline)
- Train Random Forest (ensemble)
- Train XGBoost (gradient boosting)
- Compare using F1-Score
- Select best (XGBoost)

### Step 4: Deployment
- Save model as pickle
- Create Flask API
- Containerize with Docker
- Ready for production

